social_posts.post_text: Annual Christmas photos with papa’s vintage red truck 🎄🎅🏻
Festive December weekends are the actual best 🎄✨
The most magical time of year ✨
Stella & Harlow’s Christmas school play 🎄✨ these girls have been practicing for weeks and did so good!
The most festive weekend of holiday pop-up bars, Christmas dance recital, downtown cookie stroll, carriage rides, Christmas pajama party and breakfast with Santa. The visit went v well for most. 🎅🏻
Finally decking the rest of these halls because sweeping up pine needles daily is a core holiday tradition. 🫠

Behind the magic is definitely a hot mess mom just trying to hold it together, forgetting the candy canes for gingerbread day at school and driving around with no gas in her car 😅 happy to know so many of you are in my corner and will be on the side of the road with me. Let’s grab drinks after our husbands come fill our tanks so we can leave our debit card at the bar. 👯‍♀️ @thepinewoodsocial sent me this festive sweatshirt and I’m in love!

Planning a festive night with four kids is like playing roulette, iykyk, but we genuinely had the BEST time at Garden Glow tonight ✨ it was our first time walking through and we’re definitely adding it to our holiday traditions!
Icing in our hair and sprinkles on the floor but for the best reason, our annual gingerbread house day was a success 🎅🏻
Sprinkling a little more holiday cheer ✨ one more week!
It’s a Holly Dolly Christmas 🎄✨

‘You’re their memories, you’re their magic, you’re their Christmas’ 🌲✨ being a mom during the holidays is the b e s t. 

Quote by @littlejemmings
Probably on the nice list 🎅🏻🌲
A little holiday home tour 🌲✨ this is our second Christmas here and it’s feels even cozier.
Baking crew 👩🏼‍🍳🍪🎄
Our little Santa baby is 8 months old 🎅🏻 She is sitting up, trying to pull up, (allegedly) saying dada and loves trying new food. We can’t wait to celebrate her first Christmas this weekend!
Christmas Eve Eve midnight diaries: that’s a wrap 🎁
May you never be too grown to search the skies on Christmas Eve ✨
Merry Christmas friends! 🎅🏻
About last night 🥂🪩✨
Happy 2023! 🥳

Excited to head into this year finally focusing on traveling and just doing fun things after so many years of welcoming new babies and building a house. No big milestones, just watching these girls grow up and trying to soak in every minute.
This age is the b e s t
OUT OF OFFICE ✌🏻January has been wild and I’m so excited to spend the weekend with these girls for a little staycation.
A fresh kitchen after finally taking down all of the Christmas stuff is giving me life ✨
The best part of snow day is the hot chocolate ❄️
Baby bear 🧸

We said goodbye to our Charlie girl today 💔 her health has been rapidly declining and we’ve wrestled with the decision for months. We are heartbroken and devastated, she has been the best dog in the entire world. She’s been through so much with us and we’ll miss her forever.
Dolly Jean is 9 whole months! She is crawling, clapping, dancing and so much fun. This age you guys 🥹 Her favorite thing is to make the girls laugh. I wish we could bottle this up.
Love month 💕
Life lately hasn’t left much time for Valentine fun but I’m trying to get out all the pink these next couple days. 💕
Galentines 💕
Happy Valentine’s Day! 💕 we are staying in tonight and eating all the chocolate and candy from their school parties, hoping to stay awake after bedtime for wine and a rom com but pretty unlikely. 🙃

Daddy Daughter Dance 2023 ✨ we had so much fun getting ready for their night out with dad, this year he had two dates. It’s Harlow’s first and Stella’s last. Hoping these girls have the best night ever at their fairytale dance.👯‍♀️
A couple pretty girls 🙃

10 months of Dolly 🥰 she is crawling everywhere, pulling up, says mama and dada but prefers her mama over anyone else 😅 she LOVES to make other people laugh with her dancing skills and has the gummiest smile.
BEST SURPRISE EVER 🐭✈️✨ Hopped on a plane this morning to spend spring break at the most magical place on earth, I’ve been planning this trip for months and SO excited it’s finally here!
Happy birthday Harlow Elle 🥳 celebrating you is so easy. We had the best day ever 🐭✨
Disneyland day 1 was magical, we are spending the day at California Adventure today 🎡
They’re just here for the Mickey shaped snacks 🐭
Our final day at Disneyland was filled with our favorite rides, more churros, meeting princesses and dancing to the parades. 🐭✨🎶
The most magical and exhausting weekend. Take the trip. Be patient. Enjoy the good moments and let go of the bad. The memories are SO worth it. 🐭🏰🎡👑✨

Harlow is S I X 🥳 This past year has been incredible for our girl. She loves school and is doing so well, she’s already reading books and doing 1st grade work. She is also making huge strides in dance, she is focused and committed to her team and her coaches. So dang proud of our sparkly little smarty pants princess.

My lucky charms 🍀🪩✨ The girls are on spring break so no school festivities today. They kept looking for the leprechaun (🫣) but I ordered some lucky charms via instacart to make a snack later and plan to stream the new movie Luck for a movie night.
Festive Friday ☘️🌈🌟
11 months with our Dolly girl 🐰 I can’t believe we are planning her first birthday. She waves, sleeps all night and had her first tooth pop through at Disneyland! #monthsofdollyjean

Meet Banks 🐾💙

A last minute decision turned into a big surprise for the girls last night. We are all smitten with our boy. #goldendoodlesofinstagram
This duo 🐶👶🏼

Easter weekend is one of my favorite weekends, I feel like it came super quick this year. Hoping for good weather and that I can find all of our Easter baskets. 😅🐰
Happy Easter weekend! 🐰🐣

Easter morning 🐰🐰🐰🐰
Happy Easter! 🐰🌷

Chloe is SEVENTEEN 🥳 We celebrated with pizza & ice cream cake listening to her favorite Morgan Wallen. We love you and holding on to this last year before adulthood so tight. 🥰
These baby sisters are now roomies and it’s going way better than I ever imagined. Excited to see them turn into besties like their older sisters. 👯‍♀️
Birthday week 🥺
Those last few days before one are probably the hardest. Excited to celebrate our tiniest girl this weekend. 🥳
Tonight we celebrated one whole year of our Dolly girl 💕
Happy first birthday Dolly Jean! I’m not sure how we got here so fast, you’re the sweetest baby and we’re so happy you’re ours. 🥰🥰

Stella’s first communion ✝️

We rounded out the busiest weekend ever celebrating Stella and all of her hard work at PSR with her first communion. So beautiful and so grown. 🥺

My tiny dancers 🩰these girls have been working so dang hard and pretty sure there’s no better feeling in the world than watching them on stage doing what they love. It’s the big girls’ first year on the competition team and they are doing amazing. Harlow learned a solo just a few weeks ago and absolutely rocked it on stage. Excited to watch their dance journey continue.

It goes fast ya’ll 🥺

12 months with the best surprise ever. Happy birthday Dolly girl, we’ll love you forever and ever. 💕
Finally feeling like spring 🌷🌷🌷

A full Mother’s Day weekend with my favorite crew 🥰 HMD!
Weekend vibes 🤩

Last day of school ✏️📓Having these girls in the same school was so fun! Stella finished up primary and will be heading to middle school in the fall, she has grown so much this year. Harlow had THE BEST kinder year ever and is having a tough time with school ending because she doesn’t want to leave her teacher or class but we are determined to make this the best summer yet. ☀️
The best weekend kickoff to summer ☀️
Let’s go girls 💃🏼🎶🤠🪩
Neon night for recital spirit week 👯‍♀️ It’s the last week of classes for the season for Harlow & Goldie. Next up is recital & nationals, they are so ready!
Happy 8th Stella Kate 🥳 You’ve turned into my little bestie and we couldn’t love and appreciate you more. Watching you grow is so fun!
It’s recital week! 🩰✨ dance photos, dress rehearsal + multiple recital shows.. this is one of my favorite weekends ever.

In my dance mom era 🩰🪩✨

We had the b e s t recital weekend with @expressions_academyofdance I’m so proud of these girls and how hard they’ve worked this year. Watching them shine on stage is my absolute favorite thing. Next up is nationals in Destin! 🌴
Spent the week at Holiday World and officially have a new summer tradition. Camping, rollercoasters, water park.. these girls had so much fun. 🎢⛺️☀️

Pool, beach, repeat ✌🏻🌴☀️
Beach babes ☀️
Goodbye Seaside, thanks for the magical memories 🌴✨

Our first trip to Seaside was amazing. We stayed in Watercolor in the coziest house, the community is adorable and close to everything. The beach and pool were just a golf cart ride away. Our favorite spot to end the night was to eat and drink our way through the Seaside downtown area. We found our favorite beach spot and can’t wait to go back. 🫶🏻
Summertime sisters 🫶🏻☀️
